  note = {
  CORE ARGUMENT: Introduces agent-centered prerogatives allowing agents to give disproportionate weight to their own projects and interests without violating morality. Argues that consequentialism's demand to maximize impartial good fails to respect the independence of the personal point of view. Proposes a hybrid theory incorporating both consequentialist and deontological elements, where agents have permission (but not requirement) to favor their own concerns up to a certain degree.

