  RELEVANCE: Willpower framework may distinguish income vs. asset-based norms based on differential effort costs. If asset liquidation requires substantially more willpower/effort than income donation (due to psychological attachment, transaction costs, irreversibility), willpower satisficing might support income-based norms as appropriately demanding given realistic effort constraints. However, this depends on empirical claims about relative effort costs of different giving implementations.

