  CORE ARGUMENT: Proposes "moving band" approach to agent-relative permissions, where the stringency of obligations varies with how much good is at stake. When small amounts of good are achievable, agents have wide permissions to prioritize personal concerns; when large amounts of good are at stake, permissions narrow and obligations become more stringent. This creates a variable threshold rather than fixed agent-relative prerogative or constant maximization requirement.

